Here are three test files designed to be run sequentially to test Create, Modify, and Delete operations using `fsrb.ps1`.

These scripts create a sandbox directory `fsrb_test_env` to avoid messing with your current files.

### 1. `test_01_create.fsrb`
**Action:** Creates 2 directories (`sub_a`, `sub_b`) inside `fsrb_test_env` with 2 files in each.

```text
fsrb_test_env/sub_a/file_1.txt
<<<<<<< SEARCH
=======
Title: File One
Status: Original
Description: This is a text file.
>>>>>>> REPLACE
fsrb_test_env/sub_a/file_2.txt
<<<<<<< SEARCH
=======
Title: File Two
Status: Original
Description: Another text file here.
>>>>>>> REPLACE
fsrb_test_env/sub_b/file_3.py
<<<<<<< SEARCH
=======
def hello():
    print("Hello from File 3")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    hello()
>>>>>>> REPLACE
fsrb_test_env/sub_b/file_4.py
<<<<<<< SEARCH
=======
x = 10
y = 20
print(x + y)
>>>>>>> REPLACE
```

### 2. `test_02_modify.fsrb`
**Action:** Modifies all 4 files.
- `file_1.txt`: Partial replacement (middle line).
- `file_2.txt`: Full file replacement (content rewrite).
- `file_3.py`: Partial replacement (modifies the function).
- `file_4.py`: Partial replacement (changes variable values).

```text
fsrb_test_env/sub_a/file_1.txt
<<<<<<< SEARCH
Status: Original
=======
Status: Modified
>>>>>>> REPLACE
fsrb_test_env/sub_a/file_2.txt
<<<<<<< SEARCH
Title: File Two
Status: Original
Description: Another text file here.
=======
Title: File Two (Updated)
Status: Completely Rewritten
Description: The content has changed entirely.
>>>>>>> REPLACE
fsrb_test_env/sub_b/file_3.py
<<<<<<< SEARCH
def hello():
    print("Hello from File 3")
=======
def hello():
    print("Hello from File 3 - UPDATED")
>>>>>>> REPLACE
fsrb_test_env/sub_b/file_4.py
<<<<<<< SEARCH
x = 10
y = 20
=======
x = 100
y = 200
>>>>>>> REPLACE
```


